{"body": "Oh shit, you're right. For some reason I had a test that checked that before and I ended up removing this code. I refactored my fix to the simplest solution but it turns out I screwed it so now it just loses the scope.\r\n\r\nI can confirm it just loses the default scope:\r\n\r\n    >> User.count\r\n       (0.5ms)  SELECT COUNT(*) FROM `users` WHERE ((`users`.`deleted` IS NULL OR `users`.`deleted` = 0))\r\n    => 5\r\n    >> User.except(:order).count\r\n       (0.4ms)  SELECT COUNT(*) FROM `users` \r\n    => 5\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2211078", "created_at": "2011-09-27T13:59:56Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3143#issuecomment-2211078", "updated_at": "2011-09-27T13:59:56Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3143, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jrom", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/aebc2d07a50011e2a30d38435fde564a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F74765968c67007219b197f4d9aafb4e2.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/received_events", "gravatar_id": "aebc2d07a50011e2a30d38435fde564a", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jrom", "type": "User", "id": 9952, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrom/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383a28bd3543c15101017f"}, "id": 2211078, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3143"}
